The Invisible Internet Project (I2P).

== Installation ==

=== Prerequisites ===

Java 7 or higher must be installed. See the [[Java User Guide]] for more instructions on how to get the system to that point.

The {{Package|net-p2p/i2p}} is currently marked as unstable. Special permission must be granted for it to install on stable {{Keyword|amd64}} systems:

{{RootCmd|echo "net-p2p/i2p" >> /etc/portage/package.keywords}}

Or:

{{RootCmd|echo "net-p2p/i2p ~amd64" >> /etc/portage/package.accept_keywords}}

=== Emerge ===

{{Emerge|net-p2p/i2p}}

== Configuration ==

=== Services ===

==== OpenRC ====

To start the i2p service when the system boots:

{{RootCmd|rc-update add i2p default}}

To start the i2p service now:

{{RootCmd|service i2p start}}

==== systemd ====

To start the i2p service when the system boots:

{{RootCmd|systemctl enable i2p.service}}

To start the i2p service now:

{{RootCmd|systemctl start i2p.service}}

== Usage ==

=== Web portal ===

Once the i2p router service has been started, simply open a web browser of choice and navigate to the local i2p portal: <code>localhost:7658</code>

